6.2. If the Licensee makes a Derivative Work or any modification based upon the
Work, this licence granted under Article 6.1 shall extend to the Derivative Work and
any such modification.

6.3. No additional permissions or authorisations are granted by the Commission
(whatsoever the nature of the rights) for any use that exceeds the terms of this
Licence. Therefore, if the Licensee combines the Work with other works or computer
programs protected by other patent claims, this licence granted under Article 6.1
shall not extend to these other works or computer programs.

6.4. This licence granted under Article 6 does not grant the Licensee any rights on
the use of the trade names, trademarks, service marks, or other distinctive signs
