Article 13
Revision of the Licence

13.1. Versions of the EUPL are numbered according to the following pattern:
"EUPL v. X.Y", where X is the major version and Y is the minor version number.

13.2. A new version of this Licence is published when changes are brought which affect
the obligations or the rights of the Licensee or the Licensor, or if the changes modify
or delete any of the essential elements of the Licence such as the scope of the rights
granted, the limitations and the obligations of the Licensee.

13.3. A new version number (X and/or Y) is assigned only when a new version of the
Licence is published. A minor version number change (Y) does not entitle the
Licensee to terminate the Licence, and a new version of the Licence shall automatically
apply to all copies of the Work that have been communicated, published or distributed
