new version to all or part of those copies of the Work.

13.4. When a new version of the Licence is published, the Licensee may continue to use
the Work under the terms of the previous version of the Licence for the duration of
the copyright on the Work.

13.5. The Commission may publish other linguistic versions of this Licence or versions
in other formats. So far as they are accurate and complete translations of the original
text, they will have the same value as the original version. In case of discrepancies
between the original English text and a translation, the original version shall
prevail.


Article 14
List of works using the EUPL

The Commission shall maintain a list of works distributed under the EUPL. Any person
or entity having knowledge of the use of the EUPL for a particular work may notify
the Commission accordingly at the following email address:
OPEN-SOURCE-SOFTWARE@ec.europa.eu


Article 15
Guiding Principles

In order to facilitate the reuse of software and promote the development of an open
source software community, the Commission, when distributing software, will in
principle use the EUPL as its open source software licence.

The use of the EUPL for a particular software code should be decided on a
case-by-case basis, with the main objective of maximising the reuse of the code and
the benefits for the public and European institutions in general.

When reusing the software, the Licensee should include a note that the Work is
originally developed by a European Union institution.


